<TITLE> US, UK confident about polls by end of 2008 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 15 (bdnews24.com)--The US and the UK have both expressed confidence that the next parliamentary elections will be held by December 2008. "I am hopeful, I am confident that the elections will be held by the end of 2008," US Charge d'Affaires Geeta Pasi told reporters Tuesday following a meeting with foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury at the foreign ministry. The purpose of the meeting was to brief the diplomats about the progress of holding general elections by December 2008. "The foreign adviser has assured us that there will be elections by December 2008," British high commissioner Anwar Choudhury told reporters after the meeting. He said the adviser had invited all diplomats based in Dhaka to brief them about the progress of holding elections by December 2008. He also discussed the caretaker government's activities in 2007, the UK envoy added. "We have to succeed in holding elections," Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury said, repeating that the elections must take place by December 2008. bdne
